{{short description|A large submarine plateau west of New Zealand and south of the Lord Howe Rise}}
[[File:Zealandia, topographic map.jpg|thumb|upright=1.35|Topographic map of Zealandia showing the Challenger Plateau]]
The '''Challenger Plateau''' is a large submarine plateau west of [[New Zealand]] and south of the [[Lord Howe Rise]]. It has an approximate diameter of {{convert|500|km|mi|abbr=on}} and an area of about {{convert|280000|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}. The water depth over the plateau varies between {{convert|500|m|ft|abbr=on}} to {{convert|1500|m|ft|abbr=on}} and is covered by up to {{convert|3500|m|ft|abbr=on}} of [[sedimentary rock]]s of Upper [[Cretaceous]] to recent in age.<ref name="Geoscience Australia">{{cite web | url=http://www.ga.gov.au/provexplorer/provinceDetails.do?eno=29476 | title=Challenger Plateau | publisher=[[Geoscience Australia]] | date=2012 | accessdate=7 September 2013}}</ref> The plateau originated in the [[Gondwana]]n breakup and is one of the five major submerged parts of [[Zealandia (continent)|Zealandia]], a largely submerged [[continent]].

