'''Estcoin''' is a proposed national [[cryptocurrency]], devised by the [[Government of Estonia]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/12/19/estonia-wants-its-own-cryptocurrency-called-estcoin-in-bid-to-become-global-ico-hub/ |title=Estonia planning its own cryptocurrency, called ‘estcoin’, in bid to become global ICO hub |author=Chris O'Brien |date=19 December 2017 |journal=[[VentureBeat]] |publisher= |access-date=19 February 2018 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bitcoin-estonia-estcoin/estonias-tech-guru-outlines-ideas-for-digital-estcoin-idUSKBN1ED1E6 |title=Estonia's tech guru outlines ideas for digital 'estcoin' |author=Francesco Canepa |date=19 December 2017 |journal=[[Reuters]] |publisher= |access-date=19 February 2018 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ccn.com/estcoin-estonia-could-soon-launch-its-own-digital-currency/ |title=Estcoin: Estonia Could Soon Launch Its Own Digital Currency |author=Francisco Memoria |date=26 August 2017 |journal=[[CNN]] |publisher= |access-date=19 February 2018 |quote=}}</ref> in August 2017.<ref name="World Finance">{{cite web |last1=Darrah |first1=Kim |title=Estonia pushes ahead in race to issue first state-backed cryptocurrency |url=https://www.worldfinance.com/markets/estonia-pushes-ahead-in-race-to-issue-first-state-backed-cryptocurrency |website=World Finance |accessdate=7 October 2018 |date=23 Apr 2018}}</ref> In June 2018, amid criticism from banking authorities, Estcoin's plans were revised to no longer [[stablecoin|peg]] its value to the euro, nor for it to be a national cryptocurrency,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ummelas |first1=Ott |title=Estonia Scales Down Plan to Create National Cryptocurrency |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-06-01/estonia-curbs-cryptocurrency-plan-that-drew-rebuke-from-draghi?srnd=cryptocurriences |website=Bloomberg |accessdate=7 October 2018 |date=1 Jun 2018}}</ref> so that Estcoin would be the official currency of its [[e-Residency of Estonia]] program.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Alexandre |first1=Ana |title=Estonia Rolls Back Its Plan to Issue National Digital Currency |url=https://cointelegraph.com/news/estonia-rolls-back-its-plan-to-issue-national-digital-currency |website=CoinTelegraph |accessdate=7 October 2018 |date=2 Jun 2018}}</ref> As will be restricted to individuals within the Estonia E-Residency program, it cannot be exchanged freely and thus technically doesn't qualify as a cryptocurrency.<ref name="World Finance" />

