[[File:Mrduja from Rt Zaglav.jpg|thumb|right|[[Mrduja]] from [[Cape Zaglav]]]] The '''Mrduja Regatta''' ({{lang-hr|Mrdujska regata}}) is an annual [[regatta]] held in the city of [[Split, Croatia|Split]], named after the [[islet]] of [[Mrduja]] in the [[Split Gates]] strait. It is contested over a course of {{convert|22|NM}}.<ref name="HRT">{{cite web|url=http://sport.hrt.hr/odrzana-83-mrdujska-regata|title=Shining-Umago pobjednik Mrduje|date=27 September 2014|work=hrt.hr|publisher=[[Croatian Radiotelevision]]|language=Croatian|accessdate=22 December 2014}}</ref>
The regatta's first edition took place in October 1927. It was not held during World War II, between 1941 and 1945. In the regatta's 75th edition in 2006, 312 sailboats took part in the race.<ref name="HRT"/>
